    "notes": "Emilian-Romagnol. Gallo-Italic language of Emilia-Romagna. ~2 million speakers. Reference variety: Bolognese. Key features: (1) Front rounded vowels /y, Гё/. (2) Phonemic vowel length. (3) Strong nasal vowels. (4) Degemination. (5) Intervocalic lenition (Hajek 1997, Loporcaro 2009).",
